Exactly what we do in Denmark - add &quot;www.&quot; to every domain on the list from the .dk domain administrator

That offcause means that we don&#39;t get content on those rare occasions where foo.bar is different from www.foo.bar - we don&#39;t consider that a 
problem at the moment

You could easily write a small shell-script checking both that things were alive and to some good extent even check if it shoud be different 
sites with and without &quot;www&quot; - before starting up heritrix

